# Conventional Commits Template
#
# Commit Format: type(scope): description
#
# TYPES:
#   feat:     New feature (user-facing functionality)
#   fix:      Bug fix (resolves issue)
#   test:     Adding or updating tests (RED phase for TDD)
#   docs:     Documentation changes
#   refactor: Code refactoring (GREEN→REFACTOR phase, no behavior change)
#   chore:    Build process, dependencies, tooling
#   ci:       CI/CD changes (GitHub Actions, build config)
#   style:    Formatting, whitespace (no logic change)
#   perf:     Performance improvements
#
# SCOPES (examples):
#   scripts-web, scenes-web, vo-web, cam-op-pwa, edit-web, translations-web, data-entry-web
#   shared (for @workspace/shared changes)
#   ci, db, deps, types, config
#
# TDD PATTERN (Encouraged for Features):
#   1. test(scope): Add failing test for X [RED phase]
#   2. feat(scope): Implement X [GREEN phase]
#   3. refactor(scope): Improve X [REFACTOR phase]
#
# DESCRIPTION GUIDELINES:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")
#   - Do not capitalize first letter
#   - Do not end with period
#   - Limit to 50 characters
#   - Reference issue numbers: "fixes #123"
#
# EXAMPLES - Conventional (✅):
#   test(scripts-web): Add failing test for comment sidebar (RED)
#   feat(scripts-web): Implement comment sidebar component (GREEN)
#   refactor(scripts-web): Extract comment logic to hook (REFACTOR)
#   fix(shared): Correct RLS policy for admin users
#   docs(coord): Update RULES.md with conventional commits standard
#   ci(github): Add commit message linter to quality gates
#   chore(deps): Upgrade Vitest to 1.0.0
#
# EXAMPLES - Non-Conventional (❌ - Avoid):
#   Updated comment sidebar
#   WIP: working on feature X
#   fix stuff
#   TEST: Add test for X  (use lowercase "test:")
#   FEAT: Implement X     (use lowercase "feat:")
#
# GIT USAGE:
#   git config commit.template /Volumes/HestAI-Projects/eav-monorepo/.gitmessage
#   (Configure once, then git commit will use this template automatically)
